Scatter Charts
Use scatter charts to show meaningful information using one or two groups of report data plus summaries.
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
For example, to see how stage duration correlates with the number of activities for opportunities, group your report by Opportunity Name and plot the scatter chart by the grouping.
You need at least one grouping in your report. Choose a report format that allows groupings, such as, summary, matrix, or joined.
This is a report on closed won opportunities grouped by account and opportunity owner. A scatter chart can reveal the potential for tapping into accounts with a higher annual revenue.

The X-axis automatically displays Record count when there are no summarized fields, otherwise it will display the first summary field.
The Y-axis automatically displays Record count when there are no summarized fields or the second summary in report charts, but you can manually choose a different summary to show on the axis.

Plot By automatically chooses the first report grouping. We manually chose the second grouping to show opportunities won by Account Name.
Group By is not set by default. Since the report has another grouping, the chart groups data further by the manually selected Opportunity Owner grouping.

The scatter chart component type in dashboards has these limitations: It doesn't show tabular reports. You can only change how Y-axis units are displayed. You can manually define the range for Y-axis alone.
